{
  "texts": [
    "For example, BERTopic architecture consists of neural (transformer-based) word embeddings, dimension reduction, and cluster analysis components for topic discovery (Grootendorst 2022).",
    "In the field of natural language processing (NLP), TM is a significant task and can be used to enhance several other NLP applications including sentiment analysis (Dandala et al. 2019; Kastrati et al. 2020; Ray and Chakrabarti 2020; Ogunleye 2021), recommender systems (Christodoulou et al. 2022; Pennacchiotti and Gurumurthy 2011), document summarisation (Ma et al. 2012; Wang et al. 2009), fake news detection (Birim et al. 2022; Casillo et al. 2021; Sabeeh et al. 2021), and chatbot (Tepper et al. 2018).",
    "Similarly, TM approaches have been used to extract coherent topics from airline customer complaints (Çallı and Çallı 2022), user satisfaction (Kim et al. 2022), bank customers' discussion (Ogunleye 2021; Ogunleye et al. 2023), mobile banking app reviews (Tabiaa and Madani 2021), and legal documents datasets (Silveira et al. 2021).",
    "Furthermore, the concept of TM is useful to detect hidden topics in open-ended text.",
    "TM is becoming popular for research review analysis (Alhashmi et al. 2023; Atzeni et al. 2022; Chen et al. 2022; D'ascenzo et al. 2024; Ding et al. 2023; Kane et al. 2016; Kee et al. 2019; Mendiratta et al. 2023; Natukunda and Muchene 2023; Ogunleye et al. 2024; Park et al. 2023; Pramanik and Jana 2023; Rejeb et al. 2023a, b; Sheng et al. 2023; Soltani et al. 2023)."
  ]
}